This Capstone Excellence Award from Western Governors University recognizes exceptional work which is worthy of being showcased in WGU’s Capstone Excellence Archives to serve as an exemplar for other students and alumni. Often students’ capstones are chosen because they provide excellent examples of the following:

expressing ingenuity through creativity, originality, initiative, or resourcefulness
exhibiting mastery through higher competency, true craftsmanship, or proficiency
enabling synergy and creating greater value by serving individuals, an organization, or their community
Other criteria are considered in the selection process for the award, including:

high scores on rubric aspects
receipt earlier of an Excellence Award
low number of submissions on capstone tasks
appropriate originality scores
completion of the capstone within a reasonable amount of time
